<event name="FLAGSHIP_CONSTRUCTION" unique="true">
	<text>You arrive at the beacon to find yourself in a huge Rebel shipyard, scaffolding and construction drones filling the entire surrounding area! The entire system looks devoted to ship construction, the nearby planets and moons ruthlessly mined to harvest resources for ships of immense size...</text>
	<img back="BACK_EVENT_CONSTRUCTIONYARD" planet="NONE"/>
	<preventQuest/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Inspect the shipyard.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You move closer to the planet's surface, noticing a giant hangar. The ships inside must be enourmous in size. Around the outskirts are a few scattered Rebel ships patrolling. You could probably pick any one of them to fight.</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Investigate the hangar.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You enter the hangar and are left in awe at the sight inside. A massive Multiverse Flagship, still under construction, rests inside. Killing this thing could save a whole other reality!</text>
					<ship load="SHIP_FLASHSHIP_CONSTRUCTION" hostile="false"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Fight the Flagship.</text>
						<event>
							<text>This could very well be just as important as your primary mission. You move in to attack the Flagship, as the crew of construction workers onboard quickly evacuate and are replaced by well trained human soldiers.</text>
							<ship hostile="true"/>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Continue...</text>
								<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Get the hell out of here.</text>
						<event>
							<text>You leave the hangar as quickly as possible and fly away from the shipyard until you're sure you're out of danger.</text>
							<choice>
								<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
								<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
							</choice>
							<choice>
								<text>Do nothing.</text>
								<event/>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Fight one of the normal Rebel ships.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You move in to intercept one of the regular Rebel ships.</text>
					<ship load="SHIP_REBEL_NORMAL_CONSTRUCTIONYARD" hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Fight one of the Elite Rebel ships.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You move in to intercept one of the Elite Rebel ships.</text>
					<ship load="SHIP_REBEL_ELITE_CONSTRUCTIONYARD" hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Fight one of the MFK Ace Rebel ships.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You move in to intercept one of the MFK Rebel ships.</text>
					<ship load="SHIP_REBEL_SELITE_CONSTRUCTIONYARD" hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Leave immediately.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You feel the mission is the highest priority and it's too risky to stay in such a dangerous location.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="FLAGSHIP_CONSTRUCTION_DONE">
	<text>You know with an infinite amount of potential realities there are thousands more Flagships out there, but without this one at least one more reality has been saved. It's a major victory, and there's countless scrap for you to collect, and even the blueprints of a Rebel cruiser left unprotected! Cautious of reinforcements arriving, you take as much as you can and leave. The Fleet will likely be too distracted dealing with this loss to follow you.</text>
