<event name="AUTO_ENGINEER_MISTAKE_QUEST">
	<beaconType id="map_icon_a55" global="true">
		<color r="255" g="255" b="255" a="1.0"/>
		<unvisitedTooltip>Location of the rogue Rebel cognitive.</unvisitedTooltip>
		<visitedTooltip>Explored location. Nothing left of interest.</visitedTooltip>
	</beaconType>
	<preventFleet/>
	<text>You've arrived at the co-ordinates given by the Engineers, but instead you've found a crashed starliner converted into a massive city bustling with pirates. A prime place to find a rogue AI, but not an easy one to search through.</text>
	<img back="BACK_EVENT_A55_CITY" planet="NONE"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Land and ask around.</text>
		<event>
			<text>Fortunately, the pirates don't really seem to care that you're a Federation officer. Living so close to Rebel space, it's probably a nice change of pace if anything. Asking around about a rogue cognitive however turns up confusing results. Most people have no idea what a cognitive is, and most redirect you to speak with the king of the city.</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Go see the king.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You step into a massive, cobbled together tower of spliced cargo containers and the hulls of former Rebel ships. In the center sits a throne, on which rests a rotund man with a black paper hat staring down upon you. He isn't particularly imposing, save for the buzzsaw that apparently has replaced his left hand. "I see yee have found me in my d-d-dominion. Welcome, matey!"</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event>
							<text>The man 'stands' up, revealing he in-fact has no feet, but rather a set of treads. He rolls towards you, and it becomes clear this is no man at all, but rather a ramshamble Doctor Drone. "Arg, I be Cap'ain A5540L3, at your service. How might I help you, lad?" The drone sticks out his left hand to shake yours before he remembers his situation, and so quickly stuffs it behind his back and reaches out his right instead, which is instead a much less imposing but still concerning blaster arm from a Battle Drone.</text>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Shake his "hand".</text>
								<event load="A55_HANDSHAKE"/>
							</choice>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Get right to business.</text>
								<event load="A55_FIGHT"/>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Avoid the city.</text>
		<event>
			<text>This mission isn't worth stirring up an entire city of pirates. You pull away from the city.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="A55_HANDSHAKE">
	<text>You carefully grab his arm cannon and shake it up and down a few times. "Arg, mighty grip you've got there, lad! Now, surely there's a reason the Federation's come prodding around here."</text>
	<variable name="loc_a55_handshake" op="set" val="1"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Explain why you're here.</text>
		<event load="A55_FIGHT"/>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="A55_FIGHT">
	<text>It doesn't take a genius to realize this is the cognitive in question, and you waste no further time explaining the situation to him. "Hmmm. Sounds grave, matey. You surely understand I'm not just gonna r-r-roll out of here with you."</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Then we have a standoff, don't we?</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Arg, it would appear so." A55 does his best to clap, then whistles. Seconds later, a massive Auto-Dreadnaught comes whirling by through a hole in the ceiling of the massive throne room. "Last chance lad, I don't wanna cause no bloodshed t-t-today."</text>
			<ship load="SHIP_AUTO_SENTIENT" hostile="false"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Prepare to fight!</text>
				<event>
					<text>Curiously, A55's massive vessel makes no attempt to fight you until you get into your cruiser, though it easily could have blown your crew away during the run. You have no time to contemplate this further, it's time to fight!</text>
					<ship hostile="true"/> 
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Leave.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Leave him alone.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You turn and walk out of the room. A55 watches you leave in mild amusement and confusion.</text>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="A55_DEFEAT">
	<text>Suddenly, the Dreadnaught shuts offline, falling to the ground. In the distance approaches the engineers from earlier, here to collect their AI. You don't have time to hail them before you receive another hail from A55. "Please matey, don't hand me over. They'll tear me apart and turn me offline! That's no proper fate for a pirate, arg!"</text>
	<variable name="ach_boss_a55" op="set" val="1"/>
	<ship hostile="false"/> 
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Hand over A55.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You grab the medic drone, carting him over to the Engineers. "He's integrated himself into a new chassis? Incredible! It's a shame we'll have to destroy it, but at least this drone will look cool as a trophy. Don't speak of this to anyone."</text>
			<autoReward level="HIGH">standard</autoReward>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Lie to the Engineers, tell them the Auto-ship is A55.</text>
		<event>
			<text>A55 hides while you inform the engineers about the Auto-ship, which they briefly scan. The engineer frowns, "Huh, I can see traces of his programming here, but it looks like the core migrated to a new chassis. This must have been a distraction, we'll have to keep searching. Here's your pay or something. Don't speak of this to anyone."</text>
			<autoReward level="LOW">standard</autoReward>
			<choice hidden="true" req="loc_a55_handshake" lvl="0" max_group="0" blue="false">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Thank you, matey. Arg, though you did choose to try and murder me a few minutes ago, your heart is clearly in the right place lad. I suspect my time here as king might be short lived, those Engineers will come around again. But as I prepare to leave, take this."</text>
					<drone name="RANDOM"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" req="loc_a55_handshake" lvl="1" max_group="0" blue="false">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Thank you, matey. Arg, though you did choose to try and murder me a few minutes ago, your heart is clearly in the right place lad. I suspect my time here as king might be short lived, those Engineers will come around again. I think I shall come with you, in hopes I might live to see a future without Rebels. Let me send you over some scans o' me ship - not the one you destroyed, but one I plundered from the Rebel databanks back in the day."</text>
					<variable name="ach_crew_a55" op="set" val="1"/>
					<unlockCustomShip silent="false">PLAYER_SHIP_AUTO</unlockCustomShip>
					<drone name="A55_BATTLE"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

