<event name="JERRY_HOME_WIN">
	<text>The Auto-ship has been defeated, and you waste no time salvaging before flying down to the landing pad where you see a team of evacuators - with high security detail, rushing to the largest cruiser available. Among them are several armed Aces, a tall and imposing commander dressed in black garments with yellow stripes, and a scruffy looking civilian. The man in black is no doubt who you're looking for. As you approach the group they draw their weapons, and you draw yours.</text>
	<variable name="loc_jerrymet" op="set" val="1"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Your time is up, Jerome! The Federation has come for you at last!</text>
		<event>
			<text>The man scoffs, pushing back his lustrous hair with his perfectly shapen fingers. "So the uncivilized Federation brutes sent by Universe 0 have gotten so brash and foolhardy they plunge themselves into matters of Vance, thinking wounding the chief of the Rebellion personally will stop his spirit or the glory of our conquest? When I heard the Federation was substituting a proper navy for rogues so loose even the Syndicate wouldn't take them, I laughed, and now I laugh twice! You are a joke! Hah!"</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>If we're a joke, then killing you is the punchline.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"HAH! So now we're being clever, why I aughta-" The man is cut off by the civilian in the back of the crowd, his green eyes poking out from underneath a mop of hair and crooked spectacles. "Sebastian, please. Let me talk to them." Seems you were wrong in your assumption, as 'Sebastian' immediately steps down and apologizes to the young man, no older than his early twenties, addressing him as none other than 'Jerome'.</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>So, you're Jerome then.</text>
						<event>
							<text>He nods. "Y-yes. Though most people call me Jerry. We meet at last, Renegade. If... if that's what you call yourself. Well. Here I am. Jerry Wentworth, in the flesh. Not what you were expecting? Never seem to be. People come from all over, and well, they set their expectations a bit high. So... you came here because you have a job to do, right? Well, go ahead." Jerry stretches out his arms as if he were giving you a hug. He's trembling, and sweating hard, but his eyes glow fiercely determined, as if you were the one on trial, not him.</text>
							<choice hidden="true" req="pilot" lvl="1" max_group="0" blue="false">
								<text>Shoot him.</text>
								<event>
									<text>You aren't going to pass up a chance like this. In one swift movement you draw your laser and shoot Jerry down. His knees buckle, his body collapses, but the look in his eyes never fades. His squad panics and call for a medical team, and you take your leave. As you go, you make sure to salvage the drone from earlier. Your mission was a success, but you can't shake the feeling that you made a mistake here...</text>
									<autoReward level="HIGH">weapon</autoReward>
									<variable name="loc_jerrykill" op="set" val="1"/>
								</event>
							</choice>
							<choice hidden="true" req="rep_jerry" lvl="0" max_lvl="3" max_group="1" blue="false">
								<text>Spare him.</text>
								<event>
									<text>You keep your hand by your side but never reach for your blaster. You look Jerry in the eyes for a solid minute before he puts down his arms. "Huh. Was this not what you came here to do? I'm giving you your chance. Aren't you going to take it?"</text>
									<choice hidden="true">
										<text>You're of more use to us alive than dead.</text>
										<event>
											<text>"How... utilitarian? Though I'm afraid I'm not of much use to you. The Rebellion calls me a hero, but I haven't the slightest idea why. I've never done much of anything. It must be nice, being you... traveling the Multiverse, being cheered at the end of your journey and feeling like you've earned it."</text>
											<choice hidden="true">
												<text>You don't think you're a hero?</text>
												<event load="JERRY_HOME_RECRUIT"/>
											</choice>
										</event>
									</choice>
									<choice hidden="true">
										<text>You aren't what we expected. Killing you doesn't feel right.</text>
										<event>
											<text>"Well, I can't say I understand where you draw the line. But I've also never been in your shoes. What's it like being a hero to your people? Like, earning that title. The Rebellion calls me a hero, but I've yet to figure out why..."</text>
											<choice hidden="true">
												<text>You don't think you're a hero?</text>
												<event load="JERRY_HOME_RECRUIT"/>
											</choice>
										</event>
									</choice>
									<choice hidden="true">
										<text>I've had a change of heart. Think I'll be one of those pacifist monk types now.</text>
										<event>
											<text>"It's a bit late for that captain, don't you think? Or... maybe not. Not sure it would be a good thing anyways. You're a hero to your people, right? And I'm a hero to mine... Not sure what's so heroic about me, but at least you've got your mission. I've got... I'm not sure."</text>
											<choice hidden="true">
												<text>You don't think you're a hero?</text>
												<event load="JERRY_HOME_RECRUIT"/>
											</choice>
										</event>
									</choice>
								</event>
							</choice>
							<choice hidden="true" req="rep_jerry" lvl="4" max_group="1" blue="false">
								<text>We've done too much to spare him now.</text>
								<event load="OPTION_INVALID"/>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="JERRY_HOME_RECRUIT">
	<text>Jerry laughs but hangs his head in shame. "No... Look, it's probably clear to you now I don't follow in my uncle's footsteps." Jerry glances back at Sebastian and the rest of his security, who've been standing there awkwardly the whole time, "But people expect me to. Just carrying this name, the Wentworth name, is enough for people to think I'm special. My mother died when I was young, and I never knew my father, but had I never met my uncle, I'd probably be like, a gardener, a chef, or a librarian. I'm not a soldier, and I'm not a politician. I'm... I'm Jerry. Nothing at all. Only thing to my name is my name itself, and I did nothing to earn that."</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Sounds like you need to take your life into your own hands.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"I'm not sure what you mean. I haven't left the Protectorate since the day I entered it. I don't have any power on this place, it's all Cyra. Vance knows I'm incompetent, and while he doesn't want the rest of the galaxy to know it, he doesn't trust me enough to keep this place afloat. Not like I could anyways."</text>
			<choice hidden="true" req="pilot" lvl="1" max_group="0" blue="false">
				<text>We can't help, nor stick around much longer, but you'll figure it out.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Maybe so. I feel like I'll be reprimanded for this later, but while I still have any grace left let me try and help you. And if you see my uncle - never forget he's a person too. He's done a lot of things, but I've seen a side to him most people never have. Don't forget it exists."</text>
					<autoReward level="HIGH">weapon</autoReward>
					<damage amount="-7"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" req="loc_killedcyra" lvl="0" max_group="1" blue="false">
				<text>You could come with us. See the Multiverse. Maybe help improve it too.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"A-are you serious? I've always wanted to- wait. This isn't some trick to lure me out of here and kill me, right?"</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Nahhhhh. Probably.</text>
						<event>
							<text>"Huh. Very reassuring. Well, it's not like things are going to improve around here. Though... a warning. Cyra isn't going to let you take me with you easily. Try not to hurt her, okay? She's only doing her job, she wouldn't hurt you unless she thought you were going to hurt me. I'm certain there's a way to get through this without any bloodshed."</text>
							<crewMember amount="1" class="unique_jerry">Jerry</crewMember>
							<variable name="loc_jerrysave" op="set" val="1"/>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" req="loc_killedcyra" lvl="1" max_group="1" blue="false">
				<text>You could come with us. See the Multiverse. Maybe help improve it too.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"N-no. I couldn't. You killed Cyra. She might have seemed cold to you, but she was like my mother. Or my aunt, I guess. I get you're just doing your job, but it just doesn't feel right. I feel like I'll be reprimanded for this later, but while I still have any grace left let me try and help you. And if you see my uncle - never forget he's a person too. He's done a lot of things, but I've seen a side to him most people never have. Don't forget it exists."</text>
					<autoReward level="HIGH">weapon</autoReward>
					<damage amount="-7"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

