<event name="JERRY_SURRENDER" unique="true">
	<text>A sprawling city has been constructed on the nearby planet, but clouds of smoke block most of your vision. As you pull closer, it is evident some major conflict has occured here. Medics hurry to treat wounded civilians left by the wayside, and burning wreckages have been haphazardly thrown into the faces of skyscrapers. Most concerningly, some of the wreckage seems to be... Federation?</text>
	<img planet="PLANET_POPULATED"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>Eventually, the civilians notice you watching them. Rather than trying to attack you, they surrender. "Please, we wanted none of this! We don't give a damn about your stupid war! Is what you've done here not enough?!"</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Accept their surrender, and the responsibility of whatever has happened here.</text>
				<event>
					<text>It's a lot of supplies for something you had no hand in - but this probably won't do anything to redeem the Federation in these people's eyes. You had no idea the Federation would sanction things like this though...</text>
					<autoReward level="HIGH">standard</autoReward>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="MORALITY_UPDATE_JERRY"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>We had nothing to do with this.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Bullshit. Even if you weren't involved in this slaughter, you still enabled it! What do you think will happen when the Federation secures its grip of this reality? They'll come back, and they'll wipe this place off the face of the galaxy. Get out of our city."</text>
					<choice>
						<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
						<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
					<choice>
						<text>Do nothing.</text>
						<event/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_CREW_MEDICAL">
				<text>(Medical Crew) Send someone down to treat the citizens.</text>
				<event>
					<text>The civilians are very reluctant to receive your help, but they're desperate for any sort of aid. "We couldn't live with not repaying this gesture in some manner... but I hope you understand just what you're fighting for. What do you think will happen when the Federation has full control of this reality? They'll come back and destroy all of us. Are you really sure you're fighting for the right side here?"</text>
					<autoReward level="MED">stuff</autoReward>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" req="BLUELIST_DRONES_MEDICAL">
				<text>(Medical Drone) Send a drone down to treat the citizens. [-1|]</text>
				<event>
					<text>The civilians are very reluctant to receive your help, but they're desperate for any sort of aid. "We couldn't live with not repaying this gesture in some manner... but I hope you understand just what you're fighting for. What do you think will happen when the Federation has full control of this reality? They'll come back and destroy all of us. Are you really sure you're fighting for the right side here?"</text>
					<autoReward level="MED">stuff</autoReward>
					<item_modify>
						<item type="drones" min="-1" max="-1"/>
					</item_modify>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="JERRY_HANGOUT" unique="true">
	<text>Several ships are docked with a small inn. You assume you won't be welcome, but curiously the people inside don't seem to care who you are. A couple Rebel officers sitting around one of the tables even wave you over. "Ey, Renegade! Come join us!"</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Join them.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You sit down at the table and one of the Rebels welcome you, clearly already a couple bottles in. "I know this is... uh... unconventional, but hell! The big man's birthday is tomorrow, it's time for celebration! You aren't... really a Fed anyways, I suppose. Heh, can't say I agree with the whole Renegade business, but meh. Not a fan of those Universe 1 folks they keep sending over either..."</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event>
					<text>You listen to the Rebels talk in mild amusement, but the inn-keeper walks by and informs you that, if you intend to stay at the establishment and hold this seat, you have to buy a drink.</text>
					<choice>
						<text>Buy a drink and keep listening.</text>
						<event>
							<text>At your decision to stay, the Rebels cheer and you each clink your mugs together and take another sip. The soldiers introduce themselves from left to right as Spike, Tuffy, and Butch.</text>
							<item_modify>
								<item type="scrap" min="-1" max="-1"/>
							</item_modify>
							<choice>
								<text>Buy another drink.</text>
								<event>
									<text>Only two drinks in, you can already feel your head getting lighter. Still, you sit at the table and listen to the cheerful conversation. Most of the talk seems to be topical - it seems they weren't lying about not liking the 'Universe 1 folks'. All three have plenty of stories to tell of entitled Aces and condottieri overstaying their welcome, thanks to uncomfortably intrusive quartering laws.</text>
									<item_modify>
										<item type="scrap" min="-1" max="-1"/>
									</item_modify>
									<choice>
										<text>Buy another drink.</text>
										<event>
											<text>Eventually, the conversation begins to shift to Vance's star nephew, Jerome. The conversation even draws the attention of a few other neighboring tables, who pitch in their thoughts. It seems everyone in the inn who cares to voice their opinion unanimously agrees that Jerome's a stellar guy. You aren't quite so sure of it yourself just yet, but this isn't the kind of company to raise such protest.</text>
											<item_modify>
												<item type="scrap" min="-1" max="-1"/>
											</item_modify>
											<choice>
												<text>Buy another drink.</text>
												<event>
													<text>Butch's words have begun to slur, but you aren't sure if it's him or you. As you wobble in your chair, the hysterical laughter has caught on to you as well. You think you catch sight of the innkeeper shaking his head and grunting in your direction, but you're too far out of it to really be sure.</text>
													<item_modify>
														<item type="scrap" min="-1" max="-1"/>
													</item_modify>
													<choice>
														<text>Buy another drink.</text>
														<event>
															<text>The laughter finally subsides, and the stories of their Jerry continue to flow without limits. You learn more about the guy than you ever thought you would, but you don't hold on to a single bit of information said for the entire conversation. You think you hear something about Jerry being the best man at Tuffy's wedding, but that doesn't make much sense. You think.</text>
															<item_modify>
																<item type="scrap" min="-1" max="-1"/>
															</item_modify>
															<choice>
																<text>Buy another drink.</text>
																<event>
																	<text>Theee converrrsatioon begggins to slooowww as reeeallity beecommmess a bllurr. Allll comprreeehennssionn youuu haad isss gonne. Youuuu donn't feeeelll soooo gggood, bbbuuttt thhhee convversationnn you cannn't underrrsstandddd haasss youu enthrrrallled...</text>
																	<item_modify>
																		<item type="scrap" min="-1" max="-1"/>
																	</item_modify>
																	<choice>
																		<text>Buyyy annnother drrrink.</text>
																		<event>
																			<text>Aerae HEreaore AERdftyo prtieasdklrtj eraejandwa Arerjalsd frtowajdf trlajwfeadt yeasn teasjfek eWai teald tghrsd. ERfgrys btyuurre hjtsd teaweetyuu hyjkuop gntsdfe. Tedfh ysfs raseasdfb yhsdsae.</text>
																			<item_modify>
																				<item type="scrap" min="-1" max="-1"/>
																			</item_modify>
																			<choice>
																				<text>ERaers eraweas wedafw.</text>
																				<event>
																					<text>You black out, eventually waking up on your ship, the walls painted a new shade of dark purple and a demolished disco ball in the center of the room. In the corner also lie the other three from earlier. They get up not much long after, only to find Butch's ship in a burning wreck. "Well, shit. Damn it, I'm not gonna be able to fix that with a hangover. Blegh... say, considering you're a Renegade, I wonder... maybe if we work together, we could get rid of these Universe 1 ships once and for all. At least, until I work up the courage to ask command for a new ship."</text>
																					<modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
																					<crewMember amount="1" class="human_soldier">Butch</crewMember>
																				</event>
