<event name="JERRY_DEPOT" unique="true">
	<text>Seems you've found some kind of Rebel depot. Dozens of transport ships travel in queues towards the central warehouses, and a couple workers on the ground carry back and forth crates of supplies. Defense wise, it's not impenetrable, but a nasty looking Ace vessel is standing guard.</text>
	<ship hostile="false" load="SHIP_JERRY_DEPOT"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Attack the depot.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You power up the weapons and engage the Ace ship to access the depot.</text>
			<ship hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Ignore the depot.</text>
		<event>
			<text>No reason for you to go causing extra problems here. You have more pressing matters at hand.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="JERRY_DEPOT_RAID">
	<text>With the ship now out the way, it becomes clear why the defense was so lackluster - the supplies stored here are nothing more than humanitarian, and the Rebel citizens are likely in dire need.</text>
	<choice hidden="false">
		<text>Steal the supplies.</text>
		<event load="JERRY_DEPOT_STEAL"/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Leave the supplies.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You came here looking for military goods, but the citizens of this place need this cargo. Better to leave it.</text>
		</event>
