<event name="ENCOUNTER_TOM" unique="true">
    <text>A strangely colored Rebel fighter rests nearby, its captain grumbling something incomprehensible. When he spots you, he shouts: "Federation ship! Do you know who I am?"</text>
    <ship load="SHIP_REBEL_TOM" hostile="false"/> 
    <choice hidden="true">
        <text>Not particularly.</text>
        <event>
            <text>"I am Tom, the true protector of this sector! That naive idiot has no idea how the Rebellion works, he's only in charge because his nepotism-supporting uncle loves him so much! Well I'll show that bastard what for... after I kill you!"</text>
            <ship hostile="true"/>
            <choice hidden="true">
                <text>Continue...</text>
                <event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
            </choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
    <choice hidden="true" req="LIST_CREW_JERRY">
        <text>(Jerry) "Hey Tom!"</text>
        <event>
            <text>"Ahaha! I've found you! You fool. Wait until Vance hears you're working aboard a Federation ship! Finally, your uncle will stop caring about you and get back to work on running this Rebellion!"</text>
            <ship hostile="true"/> 
            <choice hidden="true">
                <text>Continue...</text>
                <event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
            </choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
</event>
<event name="DESTROYED_TOM">
	<text>Just as you defeat the Rebel ship, an escape pod ejects from it. Unfortunately, it doesn't get far before you collect it and bring it aboard. You open it and drag out the Rebel officer inside. They beg that you let them live.</text>
	<autoReward level="LOW">standard</autoReward>
	<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_CHECK_ANY_CREW" lvl="1" blue="false">
		<text>Accept him onto your ship.</text>
		<event load="DESTROYED_TOM_POD_ACCEPT"/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_CHECK_ANY_CREW" lvl="0" max_lvl="0" blue="false">
		<text>Accepting the Rebel without further means of ensuring his loyalty is too risky.</text>
		<event load="OPTION_INVALID"/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="mind">
		<text>(Mind Control) Keep the mind control online in-case he does anything bad.</text>
		<event load="DESTROYED_TOM_POD_MIND"/>
	</choice>
		<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Free the Rebel and let them go.</text>
		<event load="DESTROYED_REBEL_POD_SAVE"/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Space him.</text>
		<event>
			<text>As you grab the Rebel by the arms and drag him into the airlock he protests little. A tear rolls down his cheek as he stands up straight and accepts his fate. You close the airlock once again when his corpse has drifted a safe distance from the ship.</text>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<eventList name="DESTROYED_TOM_POD_ACCEPT">
	<event>
		<text>The Rebel is grateful for you sparing him, despite it meaning he must betray his original cause.</text>
		<crewMember amount="1" class="human_soldier">Tom</crewMember>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>The Rebel puts on a facade of gratitude, which is shattered quickly when he pulls out a laser and blasts one of your crew! He shouts, "Rebellion forever!" before he is shot in return. You drag his lifeless body to the airlock and send him into the endless vacuum of space.</text>
		<removeCrew>
			<clone>true</clone>
			<text>Luckily, your killed crewmember is already undergoing the cloning process.</text>
		</removeCrew>
	</event>
</eventList>
<eventList name="DESTROYED_TOM_POD_MIND">
	<event>
		<text>The Rebel is grateful for you sparing him, despite it meaning he must betray his original cause. Looks like we won't need the mind control after all.</text>
		<crewMember amount="1" class="human_soldier">Tom</crewMember>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>The Rebel puts on a facade of gratitude, which is shattered quickly when he pulls out a laser and tries to shoot one of your crew! Luckily, the mind control stops him and he drops to the floor. You hurry to drag him out the airlock.</text>
	</event>
</eventList>

<event name="ENCOUNTER_MV_JERRY">
	<text load="TEXT_ENCOUNTER_MV_JERRY"/>
	<ship load="SHIP_REBEL_MV_FIGHT" hostile="true"/> 
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_CREW_JERRY">
		<text>(Jerry) "Hello!"</text>
		<event>
			<text load="TEXT_ENCOUNTER_REBEL_JERRY_HELLO"/>
			<ship hostile="false"/> 
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<textList name="TEXT_ENCOUNTER_MV_JERRY">
	<text>"Bah, we didn't come to this reality to visit Jerry just to find Federation filth here instead! Out of our way!"</text>
	<text>The Rebel ship at this beacon is no standard vessel - it's a Multiverse traveler like you, and it appears they're hungry for some Federation blood!</text>
	<text>It makes sense for there to be heavy Rebel influence in this sector, but you didn't expect to be finding a Multiverse vessel!</text>
	<text>"Finally we've found you!... wait, is this Jerry's sector? God damn it, now you've done it! If you've done anything to Jerry I swear to god that'll be the end of you! Well, I'm going to kill you either way, but you get the idea."</text>
</textList>

<event name="ENCOUNTER_REBEL_JERRY">
	<text load="TEXT_ENCOUNTER_REBEL_JERRY"/>
	<ship load="SHIP_REBEL_FIGHT" hostile="true"/> 
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_CREW_JERRY">
		<text>(Jerry) "Hello!"</text>
		<event>
			<text load="TEXT_ENCOUNTER_REBEL_JERRY_HELLO"/>
			<ship hostile="false"/> 
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<textList name="TEXT_ENCOUNTER_REBEL_JERRY">
	<text>You are traveling in a Rebel sector with security measures akin to their Stronghold, so it should be no surprise that you've run into a ship that actually wants you dead!</text>
	<text>A Rebel ship approaches: you already know what to expect with these kind of encounters. Get ready for combat!</text>
	<text>It seems this sector is not without threat after all - a Rebel ship approaches!</text>
	<text>"Hey, you're not one of Jerry's friends! Who let you in here?" A Rebel ship attacks out of nowhere.</text>
	<text>It seems your travel through this elusive sector will have to take a pause - a Rebel ship is inbound!</text>
</textList>
<textList name="TEXT_ENCOUNTER_REBEL_JERRY_HELLO">
	<text>"Jerry?! Hey man, how's it hanging!" The Rebels are no longer trying to fight.</text>
	<text>The Rebels are delighted to see their friend, and power off their weapons.</text>
	<text>As soon as they see Jerry on your ship, the Rebels no longer seem to want to fight.</text>
</textList>

<event name="ENCOUNTER_AUTO_JERRY">
	<text load="TEXT_ENCOUNTER_AUTO_JERRY"/>
	<ship load="SHIP_AUTO_FIGHT" hostile="true"/> 
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
	</choice>
</event>
<textList name="TEXT_ENCOUNTER_AUTO_JERRY">
	<text>"Prime Directive: protect Jerome from intruding Federation vessel. Do not resist destruction."</text>
	<text>It's no surprise to find an Auto-ship in Rebel space, but for some reason you weren't expecting one here. Prepare for battle!</text>
	<text>"Warning: Unwelcome Federation ship has entered the Jerome Protectorate. Please evacuate the system." The Auto-ship nearby scans your ship. "Oh. Warning: unwelcome Federation ship identified. Entering combat mode."</text>
	<text>"Critical problem, Federation ship detected, threat to Jerome at least 2%. This risk has been deemed unsatisfactorily high. Preparing to exterminate."</text>
</textList>




